1
00:01:37,090 --> 00:01:40,130
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:43,120
[Episode 2]

3
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,890
Om mani padme hum.

4
00:02:16,550 --> 00:02:17,390
May you soon be liberated

5
00:02:17,390 --> 00:02:19,520
from the Six Realms of Reincarnation.

6
00:04:11,590 --> 00:04:12,250
Don't move!

7
00:04:13,020 --> 00:04:13,680
Dongzhiba!

8
00:05:55,990 --> 00:05:57,790
There's only food and gasoline.

9
00:06:08,870 --> 00:06:10,730
You're from the Mountain Patrol?

10
00:06:17,230 --> 00:06:18,760
How did you find this place?

11
00:06:20,350 --> 00:06:21,030
By chance.

12
00:06:26,130 --> 00:06:27,330
Where are the others?

13
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:30,130
I don't know.

14
00:06:34,690 --> 00:06:35,220
Boss,

15
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:36,640
she looks like a cop.

16
00:06:48,110 --> 00:06:49,190
Are you a cop?

17
00:06:54,260 --> 00:06:54,820
Yes.

18
00:07:09,810 --> 00:07:11,140
What are you looking at?

19
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:13,770
Ju?

20
00:07:15,170 --> 00:07:16,000
Go to work.

21
00:08:28,330 --> 00:08:29,820
The Mountain Patrol is here!

22
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:31,420
The Mountain Patrol is here!

23
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,679
Pack up the pelts.

24
00:08:33,669 --> 00:08:34,200
Let's go.

25
00:08:42,740 --> 00:08:43,340
Bai Ji!

26
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:20,790
The Mountain Patrol is here!

27
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:28,200
Ju!

28
00:09:29,150 --> 00:09:29,670
Ju!

29
00:09:31,010 --> 00:09:31,460
Ju!

30
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:32,510
Are you okay?

31
00:09:32,890 --> 00:09:33,910
Ju. Ju.

32
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:35,360
Ju.

33
00:09:35,860 --> 00:09:36,630
Are you okay?

34
00:09:36,940 --> 00:09:37,370
Ju.

35
00:11:45,350 --> 00:11:46,170
Grandma.

36
00:11:47,970 --> 00:11:48,860
I'm sorry.

37
00:11:49,870 --> 00:11:52,670
I didn't take good care of Dongzhiba.

38
00:11:54,260 --> 00:11:56,090
Don't say that.

39
00:11:56,530 --> 00:11:57,340
Dongzhiba followed

40
00:11:57,340 --> 00:11:58,960
the person he respected most.

41
00:11:58,960 --> 00:11:59,870
And now he has gone

42
00:11:59,870 --> 00:12:01,550
to the place he wanted to go.

43
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:03,510
This is his karma,

44
00:12:03,620 --> 00:12:05,700
his destiny.

45
00:12:05,860 --> 00:12:09,050
May the Buddha bless him.

46
00:12:27,180 --> 00:12:29,420
May his soul ascend to heaven safely.

47
00:13:58,850 --> 00:14:00,780
Burn them even if you can't bear to.

48
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:03,330
Don't disturb his reincarnation.

49
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:31,270
What are you doing?

50
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:31,970
Move!

51
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:44,600
What are you doing?

52
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:45,310
Don't fight!

53
00:14:45,310 --> 00:14:45,790
Why are you fighting?

54
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:47,050
Who wants to fight him?

55
00:14:47,220 --> 00:14:48,790
Move. I want to go home.

56
00:14:49,170 --> 00:14:49,620
You brat.

57
00:14:49,620 --> 00:14:50,740
You coward.

58
00:14:50,770 --> 00:14:52,120
What's the use of having guts?

59
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:53,240
Today, it was Dongzhiba who died.

60
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:53,720
Tomorrow, who knows

61
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:55,250
which one of us will be next?

62
00:14:56,370 --> 00:14:57,290
Are you quitting, too?

63
00:14:57,290 --> 00:14:58,250
Then tell me,

64
00:14:58,600 --> 00:14:59,790
are sheep's lives more important

65
00:14:59,790 --> 00:15:00,740
than human lives?

66
00:15:00,740 --> 00:15:01,340
The people who killed him

67
00:15:01,340 --> 00:15:02,840
are still in the mountains.

68
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:03,460
If you leave like this,

69
00:15:03,460 --> 00:15:04,980
you're no bro of Dongzhiba.

70
00:15:04,980 --> 00:15:06,710
If you want to go back in, you go.

71
00:15:07,170 --> 00:15:08,270
They each have a submachine gun

72
00:15:08,270 --> 00:15:09,140
and semi-automatics,

73
00:15:09,140 --> 00:15:10,500
and they've got an endless supply of ammo.

74
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:11,300
But look at us.

75
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:13,510
We have just these few broken guns.

76
00:15:13,510 --> 00:15:14,330
The ammo ran out before we even

77
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:15,440
made it out of the mountains.

78
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:16,640
Even if you find them,

79
00:15:16,820 --> 00:15:17,770
what will you use to fight against them?

80
00:15:17,770 --> 00:15:18,700
Stones?

81
00:15:18,910 --> 00:15:19,930
Just like Dongzhiba?

82
00:15:19,930 --> 00:15:22,040
I'll teach you a lesson for your dad!

83
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:36,850
What's going on downstairs?

84
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:39,750
Liu and Jiumei wanted to leave,

85
00:15:40,260 --> 00:15:42,320
but Zhacuo got into a fight with them.

86
00:15:43,460 --> 00:15:44,990
Then why didn't you go help?

87
00:15:48,010 --> 00:15:48,890
You still haven't returned

88
00:15:48,890 --> 00:15:49,820
that copy of Light Weapons

89
00:15:49,820 --> 00:15:51,020
you borrowed from me.

90
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:54,130
I haven't finished reading it yet.

91
00:15:55,130 --> 00:15:56,460
I want it now.

92
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:11,690
Are you leaving?

93
00:16:15,940 --> 00:16:17,340
Aren't you leaving, too?

94
00:16:25,350 --> 00:16:26,480
Climb over the wall.

95
00:16:27,870 --> 00:16:28,930
Don't use the door.

96
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:46,350
The Public Security Bureau
is organizing an arrest

97
00:16:46,350 --> 00:16:48,950
and setting up checkpoints
on all major roads.

98
00:16:49,550 --> 00:16:50,670
But the suspect

99
00:16:50,690 --> 00:16:52,020
hasn't been caught yet.

100
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,630
I take full responsibility

101
00:16:59,850 --> 00:17:00,910
for this incident.

102
00:17:01,380 --> 00:17:02,620
[Party Secretary of Mazhi
County Party Committee, Chen Cheng]

103
00:17:02,620 --> 00:17:03,820
We set off too hastily

104
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:04,859
and didn't have time to prepare

105
00:17:04,859 --> 00:17:05,859
enough supplies.

106
00:17:06,530 --> 00:17:07,900
This caused Comrade Dongzhiba

107
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:10,560
and Bai Ju to be
in life-threatening situation.

108
00:17:11,770 --> 00:17:13,550
I will accept whatever punishment

109
00:17:13,550 --> 00:17:15,010
the higher-ups hand down.

110
00:17:15,250 --> 00:17:16,349
The county is aware

111
00:17:16,740 --> 00:17:18,440
of the Mountain Patrol's difficulties.

112
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:19,680
As for the county's difficulties,

113
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:22,339
Deputy County Mayor Duo
surely knows them, too.

114
00:17:22,980 --> 00:17:23,810
This meeting

115
00:17:24,359 --> 00:17:26,150
is not just
about assigning responsibility.

116
00:17:26,150 --> 00:17:26,900
We also need to decide

117
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:28,050
what to do next.

118
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,000
County Mayor Lin,

119
00:17:32,530 --> 00:17:33,990
why don't you speak first?

120
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,920
The Mazhi County
Economic Development Company

121
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:43,250
has been established
for a year and a half.

122
00:17:43,310 --> 00:17:45,240
And the county finance department

123
00:17:45,260 --> 00:17:46,580
allocated funds four times,

124
00:17:46,580 --> 00:17:48,990
totaling 236,800 yuan.

125
00:17:50,100 --> 00:17:51,030
Is that correct?

126
00:17:52,050 --> 00:17:53,050
At the beginning,

127
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:55,900
we brought in an external company

128
00:17:56,120 --> 00:17:58,160
to attempt silver mining.

129
00:17:58,940 --> 00:17:59,470
However,

130
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:00,920
due to inaccurate survey reports

131
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,580
and substandard ore quality,

132
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:05,180
it ultimately failed.

133
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:07,110
We still owe that company

134
00:18:07,110 --> 00:18:08,240
over a million yuan.

135
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:09,960
Besides that,

136
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,670
we haven't produced a single

137
00:18:11,700 --> 00:18:12,380
valuable

138
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:13,260
survey report.

139
00:18:15,070 --> 00:18:15,810
So I want to ask,

140
00:18:15,810 --> 00:18:16,550
Deputy County Mayor Duojie,

141
00:18:16,550 --> 00:18:17,950
what have you been doing?

142
00:18:20,620 --> 00:18:22,020
I admit that I have failed

143
00:18:22,290 --> 00:18:23,020
in my duties.

144
00:18:23,290 --> 00:18:24,660
But as work progressed,

145
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:26,270
we found that the Uninhabited Zone

146
00:18:26,270 --> 00:18:27,170
is not

147
00:18:27,190 --> 00:18:28,390
what we imagined it to be.

148
00:18:28,390 --> 00:18:29,160
So our work plan

149
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:30,480
and scope

150
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,130
have to be adjusted.

151
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:35,620
The current Bolamula

152
00:18:35,790 --> 00:18:37,530
isn't some uninhabited zone anymore.

153
00:18:37,530 --> 00:18:38,720
It's full of people—

154
00:18:39,590 --> 00:18:40,570
Antelope poachers,

155
00:18:40,570 --> 00:18:41,420
brine shrimp catchers,

156
00:18:41,420 --> 00:18:42,520
and placer gold panners.

157
00:18:42,520 --> 00:18:43,090
These are all

158
00:18:43,090 --> 00:18:44,200
tangible profits.

159
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:46,090
Right now, the priority

160
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,330
isn't development.

161
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:48,570
Our most urgent crisis is

162
00:18:48,570 --> 00:18:49,480
that we can't even guarantee

163
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:50,540
the most basic laws

164
00:18:50,570 --> 00:18:52,030
and regulations here.

165
00:18:52,140 --> 00:18:54,140
Who's stopping you from cracking down on crime?

166
00:18:54,140 --> 00:18:55,270
Who's stopping you?

167
00:18:56,070 --> 00:18:57,290
I know it's chaotic in there,

168
00:18:57,290 --> 00:18:58,110
but why?

169
00:18:58,140 --> 00:18:59,810
Isn't it because people are poor?

170
00:18:59,810 --> 00:19:00,370
Isn't it all

171
00:19:00,370 --> 00:19:01,030
because the county's economy

172
00:19:01,030 --> 00:19:01,810
can't grow?

173
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:03,500
Everyone wants to live a good life.

174
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:04,190
Tell me,

175
00:19:04,220 --> 00:19:05,280
what is a good life?

176
00:19:07,090 --> 00:19:09,020
Are people ever really satisfied?

177
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:09,920
People's desires

178
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:11,610
is just like the Uninhabited Zone,

179
00:19:11,610 --> 00:19:12,270
boundless.

180
00:19:12,270 --> 00:19:13,330
Alright, alright.

181
00:19:13,980 --> 00:19:15,840
Arguing won't solve the problem.

182
00:19:18,120 --> 00:19:19,120
County Mayor Lin,

183
00:19:19,610 --> 00:19:21,010
let's hear your opinion.

184
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:27,700
My proposal is

185
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:31,440
to disband the Mountain Patrol,

186
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:34,070
cut all

187
00:19:34,180 --> 00:19:35,750
county funding

188
00:19:35,850 --> 00:19:36,810
for it,

189
00:19:37,490 --> 00:19:40,230
and reorganize a geological survey team

190
00:19:41,030 --> 00:19:42,490
to produce a survey report

191
00:19:42,550 --> 00:19:43,880
as quickly as possible.

192
00:19:50,050 --> 00:19:52,100
Then let's follow
the organizational protocol

193
00:19:52,100 --> 00:19:54,500
and decide this through a democratic vote.

194
00:19:54,550 --> 00:19:56,680
Those who agree with County Mayor Lin,

195
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:58,100
please raise your hands.

196
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:22,670
Six votes. Passed.

197
00:20:22,850 --> 00:20:23,720
Next item.

198
00:20:29,460 --> 00:20:30,710
Deputy County Mayor Duo.

199
00:20:30,710 --> 00:20:32,110
Deputy County Mayor Duo.

200
00:20:32,530 --> 00:20:33,930
Deputy County Mayor Duo.

201
00:20:37,470 --> 00:20:38,320
Next item.

202
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:43,800
Feng Keqing
from the Xihai Chamber of Commerce

203
00:20:44,940 --> 00:20:46,270
contacted me recently.

204
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:47,850
He wants to organize

205
00:20:47,870 --> 00:20:48,400
a site visit

206
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:49,640
to Mazhi County

207
00:20:49,660 --> 00:20:51,190
and its surrounding areas.

208
00:20:52,270 --> 00:20:53,440
Isn't he

209
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:55,060
in the restaurant business?

210
00:20:55,510 --> 00:20:56,770
Does he do mining, too?

211
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:00,610
I guess he's just a middleman.

212
00:21:00,610 --> 00:21:01,730
He's acting as a go-between,

213
00:21:01,730 --> 00:21:03,330
trying to make a commission.

214
00:21:05,660 --> 00:21:06,810
Regardless,

215
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,420
it's a rare opportunity.

216
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,800
The altitude here is so high.

217
00:21:11,390 --> 00:21:13,250
Make sure they're well received.

218
00:21:33,010 --> 00:21:34,610
I went down to get something.

219
00:21:34,850 --> 00:21:36,310
Let's stick to the agenda.

220
00:21:36,660 --> 00:21:37,660
Please continue.

221
00:21:52,420 --> 00:21:54,020
If you're not going to speak,

222
00:21:54,290 --> 00:21:54,830
fine,

223
00:21:55,740 --> 00:21:57,000
then I'll speak first.

224
00:22:02,910 --> 00:22:03,860
I brought you some

225
00:22:03,860 --> 00:22:05,660
local specialties from Bolamula.

226
00:22:05,660 --> 00:22:06,460
Share them.

227
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:08,830
Good stuff. They're valuable.

228
00:22:09,270 --> 00:22:10,460
Duojie, what are you doing?

229
00:22:10,460 --> 00:22:11,790
I won't waste your time.

230
00:22:13,330 --> 00:22:15,170
Since you can't go see for yourselves,

231
00:22:15,170 --> 00:22:16,900
I brought it here for you to see.

232
00:22:17,150 --> 00:22:18,330
What it's really like

233
00:22:18,330 --> 00:22:19,440
inside Bolamula.

234
00:22:23,090 --> 00:22:23,510
The Tibetan antelope

235
00:22:23,510 --> 00:22:24,400
is a rare species

236
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:26,130
on the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau.

237
00:22:26,830 --> 00:22:28,760
At the scene where Dongzhiba died,

238
00:22:28,830 --> 00:22:29,750
the poachers killed

239
00:22:29,750 --> 00:22:31,420
364 Tibetan antelopes.

240
00:22:32,420 --> 00:22:33,030
Over 100 of them

241
00:22:33,030 --> 00:22:34,430
hadn't been skinned yet.

242
00:22:34,710 --> 00:22:35,270
This is only

243
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:36,350
a fraction of it.

244
00:22:40,330 --> 00:22:41,930
This single sheepskin alone

245
00:22:42,610 --> 00:22:44,990
goes for eighty dollars
on the black market,

246
00:22:44,990 --> 00:22:45,690
which is

247
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:46,980
over six hundred yuan.

248
00:22:48,890 --> 00:22:49,790
How much does a local earn

249
00:22:49,790 --> 00:22:51,190
working for a whole year?

250
00:22:51,790 --> 00:22:53,190
Imagine the temptation.

251
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:54,330
If no one patrols

252
00:22:54,330 --> 00:22:55,590
the Uninhabited Zone,

253
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:56,620
the poachers will do anything

254
00:22:56,620 --> 00:22:57,990
for money.

255
00:22:58,340 --> 00:22:59,100
Before long,

256
00:22:59,250 --> 00:22:59,760
the Tibetan antelope

257
00:22:59,760 --> 00:23:01,070
will be wiped out!

258
00:23:01,660 --> 00:23:02,810
What will be next—

259
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,050
Tibetan sand fox,

260
00:23:04,050 --> 00:23:04,650
wild yaks,

261
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:05,720
or snow leopards?

262
00:23:06,010 --> 00:23:06,640
When these animals

263
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:07,680
are all slaughtered,

264
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:08,530
what will be left

265
00:23:08,530 --> 00:23:10,260
on the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau?

266
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:11,110
Now,

267
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:12,820
they even dare to kill people!

268
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:16,010
I did say

269
00:23:17,350 --> 00:23:18,110
we can't modernize

270
00:23:18,110 --> 00:23:19,750
just by relying on livestock.

271
00:23:19,750 --> 00:23:20,480
Mazhi County

272
00:23:20,530 --> 00:23:22,060
has no future, just staring

273
00:23:22,090 --> 00:23:23,330
at the backs of cows and sheep.

274
00:23:23,330 --> 00:23:24,680
But the problem now is,

275
00:23:25,110 --> 00:23:26,360
we can't even protect
the native wild herds

276
00:23:26,360 --> 00:23:27,660
that have lived here

277
00:23:27,790 --> 00:23:28,940
for generations!

278
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:29,780
Comrades!

279
00:23:35,110 --> 00:23:35,830
I am a member of the Mazhi County
Party Standing Committee

280
00:23:35,830 --> 00:23:37,290
and a Deputy County Mayor.

281
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:40,980
I accept

282
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:43,660
the County Party Committee's
democratic vote.

283
00:23:46,310 --> 00:23:47,640
You can cut the funding,

284
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:49,350
but this work

285
00:23:49,660 --> 00:23:50,790
must go on.

286
00:23:53,770 --> 00:23:55,500
If the county won't approve it,

287
00:23:56,380 --> 00:23:57,880
I'll take those kids

288
00:23:57,980 --> 00:23:59,570
and keep this going as a civilian group.

289
00:23:59,570 --> 00:24:00,450
and keep this work

290
00:24:00,450 --> 00:24:00,980
going.

291
00:24:01,140 --> 00:24:02,070
Comrade Duojie,

292
00:24:02,530 --> 00:24:03,860
what do you mean by that?

293
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:04,690
Bolamula

294
00:24:04,700 --> 00:24:05,760
doesn't belong to you alone.

295
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:06,960
Stop playing the hero.

296
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:07,480
Enough.

297
00:24:08,270 --> 00:24:09,470
Sit down, both of you.

298
00:24:10,980 --> 00:24:11,700
Sit down.

299
00:24:24,050 --> 00:24:25,380
Deputy County Mayor Duo

300
00:24:25,570 --> 00:24:26,290
had a point.

301
00:24:27,150 --> 00:24:29,200
Poaching is a crime.

302
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:31,110
Fighting crime

303
00:24:31,350 --> 00:24:33,350
is the Party and government's duty.

304
00:24:33,570 --> 00:24:34,570
County Mayor Lin,

305
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:35,880
what do you think?

306
00:24:38,680 --> 00:24:40,510
County Mayor Lin's suggestions just now

307
00:24:40,510 --> 00:24:42,270
were simply planning for the county's

308
00:24:42,270 --> 00:24:43,330
long-term future.

309
00:24:44,070 --> 00:24:45,470
Deputy County Mayor Duo,

310
00:24:46,180 --> 00:24:47,180
what do you think?

311
00:24:54,610 --> 00:24:55,040
As for

312
00:24:55,070 --> 00:24:55,630
whether to keep

313
00:24:55,630 --> 00:24:56,830
the Mountain Patrol,

314
00:24:57,510 --> 00:24:58,140
the County Party Committee can discuss it

315
00:24:58,140 --> 00:24:59,400
and vote again.

316
00:25:00,370 --> 00:25:01,070
But

317
00:25:01,580 --> 00:25:03,380
the county needs to see results.

318
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:05,060
How about this?

319
00:25:06,250 --> 00:25:07,650
I'll give you a deadline.

320
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:09,530
One month.

321
00:25:10,330 --> 00:25:11,200
In a month,

322
00:25:11,970 --> 00:25:13,180
no matter how far along

323
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:14,220
your survey is,

324
00:25:15,030 --> 00:25:16,460
whether it's fifty percent

325
00:25:16,460 --> 00:25:17,440
fifty percent or thirty

326
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:18,250
you turn it in.

327
00:25:19,350 --> 00:25:21,240
That way, the investment promotion work

328
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:22,240
can move forward.

329
00:25:23,370 --> 00:25:25,300
Then we can report to our superiors

330
00:25:25,940 --> 00:25:27,270
and ask for more support

331
00:25:27,350 --> 00:25:28,750
for the Mountain Patrol.

332
00:25:30,350 --> 00:25:31,680
Okay, Party Secretary.

333
00:25:33,090 --> 00:25:35,090
The Mountain Patrol's
mineral exploration plan

334
00:25:35,090 --> 00:25:35,890
won't change.

335
00:25:42,550 --> 00:25:43,460
Sangba!

336
00:25:44,070 --> 00:25:44,770
Stop!

337
00:25:46,110 --> 00:25:47,960
Sangba, stop!

338
00:25:50,870 --> 00:25:51,440
What are you doing?

339
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:52,520
Even you are leaving?

340
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:54,170
Are you a Khampa or not?

341
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:55,680
Sangba.

342
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:56,610
You always said

343
00:25:56,610 --> 00:25:57,940
what we do is meaningful

344
00:25:57,960 --> 00:25:59,590
and that you like being with everyone.

345
00:25:59,590 --> 00:26:00,260
Why are you leaving?

346
00:26:00,260 --> 00:26:01,610
Are you afraid to die, too?

347
00:26:01,610 --> 00:26:02,810
I'm not afraid to die.

348
00:26:02,810 --> 00:26:04,050
But I came here to work

349
00:26:04,250 --> 00:26:05,720
because I wanted a permanent position.

350
00:26:05,720 --> 00:26:07,050
Don't you guys want one?

351
00:26:07,070 --> 00:26:08,660
I don't!

352
00:26:08,910 --> 00:26:09,520
Zhacuo.

353
00:26:09,600 --> 00:26:10,920
Didn't the Captain say so?

354
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:12,050
When the Economic Development Zone
is established,

355
00:26:12,050 --> 00:26:13,400
we'll all get permanent positions.

356
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:14,290
Don't you trust the Captain?

357
00:26:14,290 --> 00:26:15,220
From the day
the Captain posted the notice,

358
00:26:15,220 --> 00:26:16,090
I came here.

359
00:26:16,420 --> 00:26:17,030
We were promised that within a year,

360
00:26:17,030 --> 00:26:18,160
an Economic Development Zone
would be set up,

361
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:19,680
along with non-ferrous metal

362
00:26:19,680 --> 00:26:20,610
and salt mining companies

363
00:26:20,610 --> 00:26:21,510
with official

364
00:26:21,530 --> 00:26:22,240
permanent positions.

365
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:23,030
But since that first six months passed,

366
00:26:23,030 --> 00:26:23,790
look at us—

367
00:26:23,900 --> 00:26:25,230
what have we been doing?

368
00:26:25,420 --> 00:26:26,330
Chasing after poachers

369
00:26:26,330 --> 00:26:27,610
and catching illegal gold panners.

370
00:26:27,610 --> 00:26:28,590
We drive a hundred out today,

371
00:26:28,590 --> 00:26:29,920
and two hundred go back in tomorrow.

372
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:31,360
The county's funding is gone.

373
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:31,900
Our monthly salary

374
00:26:31,900 --> 00:26:33,180
is only two hundred yuan,

375
00:26:33,180 --> 00:26:34,160
yet we have to wait

376
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:35,310
four or five months
just to see a single cent.

377
00:26:35,310 --> 00:26:35,980
I wanted to pass the adult self-study exam

378
00:26:35,980 --> 00:26:36,980
while on the team.

379
00:26:37,110 --> 00:26:38,050
If I couldn't be a manager later,

380
00:26:38,050 --> 00:26:39,090
being an office clerk

381
00:26:39,090 --> 00:26:39,640
would have been fine.

382
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:40,290
Now,

383
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:41,370
even if I pass the exam,

384
00:26:41,370 --> 00:26:42,210
do I still have to go in there

385
00:26:42,210 --> 00:26:43,810
and catch poachers with you?

386
00:26:44,030 --> 00:26:44,520
Can catching poachers

387
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:46,120
get us a permanent position?

388
00:26:46,510 --> 00:26:47,900
Permanent position?

389
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:48,770
Do you believe it?

390
00:26:48,770 --> 00:26:50,970
I'll teach you a lesson for your father.

391
00:26:51,810 --> 00:26:52,480
Zhacuo.

392
00:26:52,510 --> 00:26:53,240
No hitting!

393
00:26:53,830 --> 00:26:54,440
Sangba.

394
00:26:54,740 --> 00:26:56,140
You're always studying.

395
00:26:56,580 --> 00:26:57,610
Have you thrown everything you've learned

396
00:26:57,610 --> 00:26:58,900
to the dogs?

397
00:26:59,000 --> 00:26:59,800
Let me ask you.

398
00:26:59,810 --> 00:27:01,290
Is the Captain a good man?

399
00:27:01,350 --> 00:27:02,210
Of course he is.

400
00:27:02,310 --> 00:27:03,290
Rain follows the clouds.

401
00:27:03,290 --> 00:27:04,310
Sheep follow the grass.

402
00:27:04,310 --> 00:27:05,030
Stop babbling.

403
00:27:05,030 --> 00:27:05,690
Spit it out.

404
00:27:06,070 --> 00:27:06,980
Good men follow good men.

405
00:27:06,980 --> 00:27:08,160
If you don't follow the good man,

406
00:27:08,160 --> 00:27:09,680
do you want to be a bad one?

407
00:27:11,340 --> 00:27:12,610
The Captain went
to the county for a meeting.

408
00:27:12,610 --> 00:27:13,520
We all know

409
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:14,050
that this time

410
00:27:14,050 --> 00:27:15,710
our unit is definitely getting disbanded.

411
00:27:15,710 --> 00:27:16,740
What's the difference between leaving now

412
00:27:16,740 --> 00:27:18,000
and leaving tomorrow?

413
00:27:20,570 --> 00:27:21,090
Let go.

414
00:27:46,430 --> 00:27:46,970
Captain.

415
00:27:59,520 --> 00:28:00,050
Captain.

416
00:28:01,010 --> 00:28:01,690
I'm sorry.

417
00:28:28,580 --> 00:28:30,380
This is the money for Dongzhiba.

418
00:28:31,050 --> 00:28:32,580
His grandma didn't take it.

419
00:28:33,220 --> 00:28:33,960
You take it.

420
00:28:37,790 --> 00:28:38,990
It's not just for you.

421
00:28:41,570 --> 00:28:42,720
If you see the others

422
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:44,610
who already left,

423
00:28:44,690 --> 00:28:46,750
make sure everyone gets their share.

424
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:57,590
My good bro.

425
00:28:59,070 --> 00:28:59,660
Go.

426
00:29:30,360 --> 00:29:30,920
Sangba.

427
00:29:43,030 --> 00:29:43,590
Captain.

428
00:29:44,310 --> 00:29:45,840
What did the county decide?

429
00:29:52,550 --> 00:29:53,880
Who is starting the car?

430
00:29:56,290 --> 00:29:57,150
Where is Bai Ju?

431
00:29:57,200 --> 00:29:58,190
She's at the station.

432
00:29:58,190 --> 00:29:59,450
Where are the car keys?

433
00:30:41,380 --> 00:30:41,990
Get out of the way!

434
00:30:41,990 --> 00:30:42,700
Get out!

435
00:30:54,850 --> 00:30:55,290
What are you doing?

436
00:30:55,290 --> 00:30:55,950
Give me the gun.

437
00:30:55,950 --> 00:30:56,510
What are you doing?

438
00:30:56,510 --> 00:30:57,440
Hurry up! Hurry!

439
00:30:58,550 --> 00:30:59,350
What are you doing?

440
00:30:59,350 --> 00:31:00,250
What are you doing?

441
00:31:00,250 --> 00:31:00,770
Leaving without a word?

442
00:31:00,770 --> 00:31:01,690
Where are you going?

443
00:31:01,690 --> 00:31:02,450
Let go of me!

444
00:31:03,330 --> 00:31:04,420
I'm going into the mountains
to find Bai Ji!

445
00:31:04,420 --> 00:31:05,440
Who authorized you to take a gun?

446
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:06,520
You left it unlocked.

447
00:31:06,520 --> 00:31:07,360
I am a police officer.

448
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:09,020
I have the right to carry a gun.

449
00:31:09,740 --> 00:31:10,670
What do you want?

450
00:31:12,860 --> 00:31:14,760
You're a cop, and you're stealing?

451
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:15,760
I'm borrowing it.

452
00:31:15,850 --> 00:31:16,710
I'll return it.

453
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:18,440
A horse without a bit won't listen.

454
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:19,010
Since when did you ever bother

455
00:31:19,010 --> 00:31:19,770
to give me a heads-up

456
00:31:19,770 --> 00:31:21,500
before coming over for dinner?

457
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:29,350
I know

458
00:31:30,290 --> 00:31:31,620
Bai Ji did those things.

459
00:31:32,770 --> 00:31:34,300
He deserves to die in there.

460
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:37,550
But he is my brother.

461
00:31:38,590 --> 00:31:39,990
Whether he's dead or not,

462
00:31:40,350 --> 00:31:41,610
I have to bring him out.

463
00:31:42,510 --> 00:31:43,200
Otherwise, I can't

464
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:44,160
face my mother.

465
00:32:01,380 --> 00:32:03,180
Where do you plan to look for him?

466
00:32:10,330 --> 00:32:11,400
This is where it happened—

467
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:12,260
Zhuoyuan Lake.

468
00:32:12,520 --> 00:32:13,440
Bai Ji ran off

469
00:32:13,480 --> 00:32:14,590
somewhere near here.

470
00:32:14,590 --> 00:32:15,510
To get out,

471
00:32:15,810 --> 00:32:17,240
the closest way is east.

472
00:32:17,700 --> 00:32:18,340
If he walk for two days,

473
00:32:18,340 --> 00:32:20,030
he'll reach the Qinghai-Tibet Highway.

474
00:32:20,030 --> 00:32:21,940
So I'll follow this route
to search for him.

475
00:32:21,940 --> 00:32:22,550
A round trip takes

476
00:32:22,550 --> 00:32:23,700
three to four days.

477
00:32:24,300 --> 00:32:25,230
Food, supplies,

478
00:32:25,290 --> 00:32:25,980
and fuel—

479
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:27,530
I‘ve brought enough.

480
00:32:27,530 --> 00:32:28,660
That's ridiculous.

481
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:30,730
If you run into a blizzard in there,

482
00:32:30,730 --> 00:32:33,190
you won't even be able
to tell the direction.

483
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:37,020
What if you run into poachers?

484
00:32:38,070 --> 00:32:39,120
I excelled in marksmanship

485
00:32:39,120 --> 00:32:40,380
at the police academy.

486
00:32:42,550 --> 00:32:43,530
The map won't tell you

487
00:32:43,530 --> 00:32:44,730
where the swamps are.

488
00:32:45,240 --> 00:32:46,080
If the car gets stuck,

489
00:32:46,080 --> 00:32:47,940
how will you pull it out yourself?

490
00:32:48,170 --> 00:32:48,770
If you meet a wolf pack,

491
00:32:48,770 --> 00:32:49,770
is one gun enough?

492
00:32:55,510 --> 00:32:56,970
I know what you're saying.

493
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:00,290
But I must go in.

494
00:33:02,110 --> 00:33:02,530
Even if there's only

495
00:33:02,530 --> 00:33:03,400
a one percent chance

496
00:33:03,400 --> 00:33:03,790
of finding him,

497
00:33:03,790 --> 00:33:04,920
I still have to go in.

498
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:07,600
If it were your family

499
00:33:07,600 --> 00:33:08,530
trapped inside,

500
00:33:09,430 --> 00:33:10,220
would you go?

501
00:33:13,670 --> 00:33:14,590
Would you?

502
00:33:19,420 --> 00:33:20,880
The team is in a tough spot.

503
00:33:21,740 --> 00:33:23,610
Going into the mountains isn't easy.

504
00:33:23,610 --> 00:33:25,270
This is my personal business.

505
00:33:25,460 --> 00:33:27,520
I have no reason to drag you into this.

506
00:33:27,770 --> 00:33:29,310
My plan isn't perfect.

507
00:33:29,890 --> 00:33:30,520
But no plan

508
00:33:30,540 --> 00:33:31,800
ever is.

509
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:33,670
I'll deal with

510
00:33:33,690 --> 00:33:35,150
the consequences myself.

511
00:33:42,700 --> 00:33:43,270
When were you planning

512
00:33:43,270 --> 00:33:44,140
to go in?

513
00:33:44,640 --> 00:33:45,090
The plan was

514
00:33:45,090 --> 00:33:45,960
that after Dongzhiba's funeral,

515
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:46,560
we'd go in.

516
00:33:47,140 --> 00:33:48,600
Now, it's time to head out.

517
00:33:49,700 --> 00:33:51,230
All her gear will be useful.

518
00:33:51,500 --> 00:33:52,360
Bring them all.

519
00:33:52,510 --> 00:33:52,900
Okay.

520
00:33:54,550 --> 00:33:55,830
Did you think the Captain

521
00:33:55,830 --> 00:33:56,380
would leave Bai Ji behind

522
00:33:56,380 --> 00:33:57,440
in there?

523
00:33:58,580 --> 00:34:00,180
It was too chaotic back then.

524
00:34:00,380 --> 00:34:01,640
You and Dongzhiba

525
00:34:01,660 --> 00:34:03,240
were both down on the ground.

526
00:34:03,240 --> 00:34:03,790
We had no choice

527
00:34:03,790 --> 00:34:05,520
but to bring you two back first.

528
00:34:08,760 --> 00:34:09,260
Yeah.

529
00:34:09,670 --> 00:34:10,679
Now that Bai is okay,

530
00:34:10,679 --> 00:34:11,900
it's time to head out.

531
00:34:20,120 --> 00:34:20,650
Let's go.

532
00:34:23,110 --> 00:34:23,710
Thank you.

533
00:34:24,380 --> 00:34:25,580
As long as you're on the team,

534
00:34:25,580 --> 00:34:26,909
you're one of my people.

535
00:34:27,389 --> 00:34:28,989
Your problem is our problem.

536
00:34:29,800 --> 00:34:30,610
Understood.

537
00:34:34,510 --> 00:34:35,040
Let's go.

538
00:35:01,740 --> 00:35:03,470
We'll drive through the night.

539
00:35:03,740 --> 00:35:06,240
and will reach Zhuoyuan Lake

540
00:35:06,880 --> 00:35:08,410
just as the sun is coming up.

541
00:35:09,730 --> 00:35:10,710
The water in that lake

542
00:35:10,710 --> 00:35:12,170
is incredibly beautiful.

543
00:35:13,340 --> 00:35:15,030
I often get up early to see it.

544
00:35:18,430 --> 00:35:19,820
Dongzhiba is gone.

545
00:35:21,610 --> 00:35:23,140
Sometimes death feels like

546
00:35:23,430 --> 00:35:24,180
someone you know well

547
00:35:24,180 --> 00:35:25,520
has just stepped out

548
00:35:25,550 --> 00:35:26,650
on a trip.

549
00:35:27,900 --> 00:35:29,630
He left without saying goodbye

550
00:35:30,550 --> 00:35:31,780
and never came back.

551
00:35:34,330 --> 00:35:34,960
The last time

552
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:36,730
someone left me

553
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:39,490
was when my father was on night shift

554
00:35:39,490 --> 00:35:40,750
and ran into a fugitive

555
00:35:42,650 --> 00:35:43,540
The last time

556
00:35:43,570 --> 00:35:44,800
I saw him,

557
00:35:46,240 --> 00:35:48,320
I saw his bloodstained uniform.

558
00:35:50,350 --> 00:35:51,330
That color

559
00:35:52,290 --> 00:35:54,690
was as red as the sunset
over Zhuoyuan Lake.

560
00:35:58,050 --> 00:36:00,710
There's no point
in trying to hold on to someone.

561
00:36:01,500 --> 00:36:03,300
Whether in the Uninhabited Zone

562
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:04,720
or a populated place,

563
00:36:06,260 --> 00:36:08,060
accidents can happen anywhere.

564
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:11,360
So, Dongzhiba,

565
00:36:12,900 --> 00:36:14,070
I've found the meaning

566
00:36:14,070 --> 00:36:15,000
of this job.

567
00:36:16,900 --> 00:36:18,610
I want to take your eyes with me

568
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:21,570
to see tomorrow's sun.

569
00:36:23,610 --> 00:36:25,570
I'll do everything within my power

570
00:36:27,510 --> 00:36:28,110
until

571
00:36:30,580 --> 00:36:31,940
the day I see the sunset

572
00:36:33,080 --> 00:36:34,540
for the very last time.

573
00:37:01,530 --> 00:37:02,030
Dad.

574
00:37:04,050 --> 00:37:04,780
You're back.

575
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:10,800
Where is your mom?

576
00:37:11,920 --> 00:37:13,320
She went to the hospital.

577
00:37:13,530 --> 00:37:14,930
What did she go there for?

578
00:37:15,420 --> 00:37:16,280
To see a doctor.

579
00:37:18,130 --> 00:37:19,390
What's wrong with her?

580
00:37:20,320 --> 00:37:21,050
I don't know.

581
00:37:23,320 --> 00:37:24,780
Why didn't you go with her?

582
00:37:26,190 --> 00:37:27,450
You didn't go, either.

583
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:33,480
Dad, what did you

584
00:37:33,480 --> 00:37:34,310
just take?

585
00:37:35,900 --> 00:37:37,110
I was looking for a book.

586
00:37:37,110 --> 00:37:38,640
That wasn't a book. I saw it.

587
00:37:42,940 --> 00:37:44,050
I lied.

588
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:47,050
I was looking for...

589
00:37:47,340 --> 00:37:48,140
Is it a secret?

590
00:37:51,550 --> 00:37:52,630
It's my secret.

591
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:56,500
Can you promise me

592
00:37:57,230 --> 00:37:58,290
don't tell your mom

593
00:37:58,440 --> 00:37:59,260
about this?

594
00:38:00,840 --> 00:38:01,230
Okay.

595
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:06,900
Here, put these in your bag.

596
00:38:06,900 --> 00:38:07,630
Remember to take the medicine I prescribed

597
00:38:07,630 --> 00:38:08,730
on time.

598
00:38:09,530 --> 00:38:10,320
Do not take the medicine

599
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:11,930
at home anymore.

600
00:38:12,370 --> 00:38:14,140
You must stop using wool.

601
00:38:14,830 --> 00:38:16,290
Use toilet paper instead.

602
00:38:16,760 --> 00:38:17,710
Before using the sanitary belt,

603
00:38:17,710 --> 00:38:18,910
remember to steam it.

604
00:38:19,500 --> 00:38:21,900
You know how to use
a menstrual belt, right?

605
00:38:24,400 --> 00:38:25,110
Yes, I do.

606
00:38:25,130 --> 00:38:26,730
Okay, hurry back now.

607
00:38:26,960 --> 00:38:28,110
Remember to come back for your follow-up.

608
00:38:28,110 --> 00:38:28,590
Okay.

609
00:38:28,980 --> 00:38:29,670
Thank you.

610
00:38:35,340 --> 00:38:36,670
You didn't go home after work?

611
00:38:36,670 --> 00:38:37,470
Have you eaten?

612
00:38:37,470 --> 00:38:38,730
I brought an extra dish

613
00:38:38,930 --> 00:38:39,740
for you.

614
00:38:41,090 --> 00:38:43,090
Fried dace with salted black beans?

615
00:38:44,460 --> 00:38:44,840
It's been years

616
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:46,040
since I last ate this.

617
00:38:47,140 --> 00:38:48,340
You've had it before?

618
00:38:49,530 --> 00:38:50,130
You didn't remember

619
00:38:50,130 --> 00:38:51,510
where I'm from?

620
00:38:54,340 --> 00:38:55,140
Right, right.

621
00:38:55,420 --> 00:38:57,200
The young lady from Nanjing.

622
00:38:57,230 --> 00:38:58,280
You're different from us

623
00:38:58,280 --> 00:38:59,340
country bumpkins.

624
00:39:00,150 --> 00:39:01,610
I thought about

625
00:39:01,710 --> 00:39:02,460
finding something rare

626
00:39:02,460 --> 00:39:04,190
to present to you.

627
00:39:04,760 --> 00:39:05,210
If you're not going to eat it,

628
00:39:05,210 --> 00:39:06,210
I'll take it away.

629
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:07,010
Put it down.

630
00:39:09,360 --> 00:39:09,820
Open it.

631
00:39:10,160 --> 00:39:11,160
Come on, try some.

632
00:39:15,740 --> 00:39:17,010
How is it? Is it good?

633
00:39:20,810 --> 00:39:22,050
It's just a little salty.

634
00:39:22,050 --> 00:39:23,210
You should be glad you've got this at all.

635
00:39:23,210 --> 00:39:24,230
Don't be picky.

636
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:25,400
Wait a minute.

637
00:39:26,690 --> 00:39:28,630
Have you seen Bai Ji
these last couple of days?

638
00:39:28,630 --> 00:39:29,340
No.

639
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:31,910
That kid.

640
00:39:32,840 --> 00:39:35,040
How many days has he been gone this time?

641
00:39:35,900 --> 00:39:37,090
It's

642
00:39:37,110 --> 00:39:38,570
five or six days this time.

643
00:39:39,920 --> 00:39:41,170
Where did he go?

644
00:39:47,380 --> 00:39:48,050
Come in.

645
00:39:49,410 --> 00:39:50,410
County Mayor Lin.

646
00:39:52,480 --> 00:39:52,840
County Mayor Lin.

647
00:39:52,840 --> 00:39:54,170
Why is your room so cold?

648
00:39:54,570 --> 00:39:55,050
Didn't Han

649
00:39:55,050 --> 00:39:56,210
send over some cow dung for you?

650
00:39:56,210 --> 00:39:56,670
He did.

651
00:39:57,200 --> 00:39:59,330
I sent it to the County Primary School.

652
00:39:59,710 --> 00:40:00,420
I still have some in my room.

653
00:40:00,420 --> 00:40:01,000
I'll go get you some.

654
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:01,930
No need, no need.

655
00:40:01,940 --> 00:40:02,940
There are many people in your room.

656
00:40:02,940 --> 00:40:04,360
Besides, there are female comrades there.

657
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:04,980
Once those two rooms

658
00:40:04,980 --> 00:40:05,840
are heated up,

659
00:40:05,940 --> 00:40:07,200
my room will be warmer.

660
00:40:08,070 --> 00:40:08,870
On that table,

661
00:40:08,900 --> 00:40:09,260
there is a report

662
00:40:09,260 --> 00:40:10,820
on reducing the animal husbandry tax.

663
00:40:10,820 --> 00:40:11,500
Take this

664
00:40:11,530 --> 00:40:12,650
to the leadership team right away,

665
00:40:12,650 --> 00:40:13,840
and get a meeting organized immediately.

666
00:40:13,840 --> 00:40:14,420
Okay.

667
00:40:16,130 --> 00:40:17,130
County Mayor Lin.

668
00:40:17,230 --> 00:40:18,280
Feng.

669
00:40:18,720 --> 00:40:19,460
Didn't you say

670
00:40:19,460 --> 00:40:20,590
you'd arrive tomorrow?

671
00:40:20,590 --> 00:40:21,900
We heard it might snow tomorrow,

672
00:40:21,900 --> 00:40:23,030
so we are here early.

673
00:40:23,460 --> 00:40:24,280
Who is...

674
00:40:24,860 --> 00:40:25,690
Let me introduce you.

675
00:40:25,690 --> 00:40:27,320
This is the person I mentioned before.

676
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:28,380
He is Zhao Yuji,

677
00:40:28,480 --> 00:40:29,000
a manager from

678
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:30,330
Tengda Mining Company.

679
00:40:30,650 --> 00:40:31,530
Welcome.

680
00:40:32,210 --> 00:40:33,590
Nice to meet you, County Mayor Lin.

681
00:40:33,590 --> 00:40:34,710
The County Mayor on horseback.

682
00:40:34,710 --> 00:40:35,590
I've heard so much about you.

683
00:40:35,590 --> 00:40:36,620
The County Mayor on horseback—

684
00:40:36,620 --> 00:40:37,340
You flatter me.

685
00:40:37,340 --> 00:40:37,940
Right now,

686
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:39,660
I'm the Zhongbu County Mayor—

687
00:40:39,910 --> 00:40:41,710
more like a beggar County Mayor.

688
00:40:41,780 --> 00:40:43,280
You've got a great sense of humor.

689
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:44,280
County Mayor Lin.

690
00:40:44,300 --> 00:40:45,360
Why does your room feel

691
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:47,020
even colder than the hallway?

692
00:40:47,440 --> 00:40:48,260
Let's sit by the stove.

693
00:40:48,260 --> 00:40:48,900
It's warmer there.

694
00:40:48,900 --> 00:40:50,330
County Mayor Lin Lin is being selfless.

695
00:40:50,330 --> 00:40:51,520
-He's given his own cow dung
-Let me do it.

696
00:40:51,520 --> 00:40:52,410
to the County Primary School.

697
00:40:52,410 --> 00:40:53,000
Here.

698
00:40:54,680 --> 00:40:55,210
County Mayor Lin.

699
00:40:55,210 --> 00:40:55,860
I'll go get some cow dung from my room.

700
00:40:55,860 --> 00:40:56,290
Okay, go get it.

701
00:40:56,290 --> 00:40:57,220
No need. No need.

702
00:40:57,360 --> 00:40:58,820
Look, isn't this a coincidence?

703
00:40:58,820 --> 00:40:59,880
When Manager Zhao came,

704
00:40:59,880 --> 00:41:01,000
he specially brought two truckloads
of coal.

705
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:02,440
It's all the best anthracite.

706
00:41:02,440 --> 00:41:03,940
The trucks are parked downstairs.

707
00:41:03,940 --> 00:41:04,510
Really?

708
00:41:04,530 --> 00:41:05,110
Look.

709
00:41:09,130 --> 00:41:10,460
That's two truckloads!

710
00:41:10,460 --> 00:41:11,960
Two full loads. Ten tons.

711
00:41:12,010 --> 00:41:13,550
That should be enough
for your winter, right?

712
00:41:13,550 --> 00:41:14,780
That's wonderful.

713
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:16,340
Zhang,

714
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:17,090
hurry, hurry.

715
00:41:17,090 --> 00:41:17,530
Well.

716
00:41:17,630 --> 00:41:18,710
Take these two truckloads of coal,

717
00:41:18,710 --> 00:41:19,420
and divide them into three parts.

718
00:41:19,420 --> 00:41:20,610
Send one part
to the County Primary School,

719
00:41:20,610 --> 00:41:21,890
and one part to the County Hospital.

720
00:41:21,890 --> 00:41:22,670
Don't worry, I'll arrange it immediately.

721
00:41:22,670 --> 00:41:23,130
Go, go.

722
00:41:24,630 --> 00:41:25,420
Manager Zhao,

723
00:41:25,420 --> 00:41:26,200
thank you.

724
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:27,820
I really...

725
00:41:28,570 --> 00:41:29,650
feel a bit embarrassed.

726
00:41:29,650 --> 00:41:30,530
You see, we...

727
00:41:31,240 --> 00:41:32,880
haven't reached
a cooperation agreement yet,

728
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:34,210
yet I'm accepting such a heavy gift.

729
00:41:34,210 --> 00:41:35,550
You're being too polite.

730
00:41:35,550 --> 00:41:36,900
Let me pour you some water.

731
00:41:36,900 --> 00:41:38,100
Thank you. Thank you.

732
00:41:39,310 --> 00:41:41,000
I heard from Feng long ago

733
00:41:41,170 --> 00:41:42,800
that your county is in difficulty.

734
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:43,490
Thank you.

735
00:41:43,510 --> 00:41:44,420
County Mayor Lin, have a seat.

736
00:41:44,420 --> 00:41:45,080
Let me do it.

737
00:41:45,670 --> 00:41:47,240
I wouldn't have known if I hadn't come.

738
00:41:47,240 --> 00:41:49,440
I didn't expect it to be this difficult.

739
00:41:49,730 --> 00:41:50,400
I've read

740
00:41:50,420 --> 00:41:52,030
that geological survey report

741
00:41:52,030 --> 00:41:52,760
Feng gave me.

742
00:41:53,340 --> 00:41:54,620
In the Bolamula area,

743
00:41:54,650 --> 00:41:57,320
there are plenty of gold, silver

744
00:41:57,420 --> 00:41:58,570
and rare metals.

745
00:41:59,060 --> 00:41:59,790
So why...

746
00:42:00,940 --> 00:42:01,940
County Mayor Lin,

747
00:42:02,010 --> 00:42:02,780
let me say something

748
00:42:02,780 --> 00:42:04,240
you might not like to hear.

749
00:42:04,840 --> 00:42:06,000
You're sitting on a gold mine

750
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:08,960
and still begging for scraps.

751
00:42:09,410 --> 00:42:10,140
Actually,

752
00:42:10,930 --> 00:42:11,450
we welcome

753
00:42:11,450 --> 00:42:13,180
all the entrepreneurs willing

754
00:42:13,300 --> 00:42:14,800
to come to our remote place

755
00:42:15,130 --> 00:42:16,050
to invest.

756
00:42:17,150 --> 00:42:17,900
And

757
00:42:17,920 --> 00:42:18,510
we believe

758
00:42:18,510 --> 00:42:19,860
those enterprises who are introduced

759
00:42:19,860 --> 00:42:20,820
by Feng

760
00:42:20,890 --> 00:42:22,550
are capable and responsible.

761
00:42:22,550 --> 00:42:23,650
You are right.

762
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:27,840
Our Xihai Chamber of Commerce

763
00:42:27,840 --> 00:42:28,880
does have a few

764
00:42:28,900 --> 00:42:29,880
high-quality enterprises

765
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:32,010
that want to come here for a site visit.

766
00:42:32,340 --> 00:42:32,780
This way,

767
00:42:32,780 --> 00:42:35,090
they can determine
their investment intentions.

768
00:42:35,090 --> 00:42:37,070
I just don't know if the county

769
00:42:37,170 --> 00:42:38,630
is available to host them.

770
00:42:57,860 --> 00:42:58,340
Hello?

771
00:42:58,610 --> 00:42:59,230
Why can't I get through

772
00:42:59,230 --> 00:43:00,170
to Deputy County Mayor Duojie's

773
00:43:00,170 --> 00:43:01,170
Mountain Patrol?

774
00:43:01,730 --> 00:43:02,460
County Mayor Lin.

775
00:43:02,460 --> 00:43:03,300
The Mountain Patrol's phone bill

776
00:43:03,300 --> 00:43:04,160
is way overdue.

777
00:43:04,260 --> 00:43:05,550
It was disconnected two months ago.

778
00:43:05,550 --> 00:43:06,510
That's ridiculous.

779
00:43:06,510 --> 00:43:07,440
Get it reconnected immediately.

780
00:43:07,440 --> 00:43:08,610
Let the Telecom Bureau come to me
for the money.
